HOUSE RESOLUTION 141
By Atchley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Lieutenant Gordon
Gwathney of Knoxville.
WHEREAS, the members of this legislative body were greatly saddened to learn of the
untimely passing of Lieutenant Gordon Gwathney of the Knoxville Police Department; and
WHEREAS, Lieutenant Gwathney was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in 1968 and raised in Sevier County, Gordon Gwathney learned the
values of hard work, integrity, and selfless service that would define his life at an early age; and
WHEREAS, Lieutenant Gwathney proudly served his country as a member of the United
States Army, a tenure that included a deployment to Korea, and later continued his honorable
service in the Tennessee National Guard; and
WHEREAS, dedicated to serving and protecting his community, Gordon Gwathney
joined the Knoxville Police Department in 1997 and rose through the ranks with distinction,
being promoted to Sergeant in 2003 and to Lieutenant in 2010; and
WHEREAS, known affectionately throughout East Knoxville as "Officer G," Lieutenant
Gwathney was beloved by the community he served; his friendly and compassionate nature,
along with his unwavering commitment to community policing, earned him the respect and
admiration of his colleagues and the citizens of Knoxville alike; and
WHEREAS, early in his career, he was assigned as the first-ever School Resource
Officer at Austin-East High School, where he formed countless lasting relationships and served
as a positive influence and mentor to many young people; and
HR0141
011278
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Lieutenant Gwathney's professional excellence was recognized by the
Knoxville Police Department, which named him Officer of the Year in 2013 and again nominated
him for the honor in 2019; and
WHEREAS, Lieutenant Gordon Gwathney leaves behind an indelible legacy of integrity
and probity in public life, compassion and loyalty in private life, and diligence and dedication in
all his chosen endeavors; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should remember the bountiful life of this exceptional
public servant and human being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor the
memory of Lieutenant Gordon Gwathney, reflecting fondly upon his impeccable character and
his stalwart commitment to living the examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we express our sympathy and offer our condolences
to the family of Lieutenant Gwathney.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
